Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.86,0:00:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Debugging with Xcode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.30,0:00:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Chris Miles and I work on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.91,0:00:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.91,0:00:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a lot of great new
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.06,0:00:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,debugging features to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.53,0:00:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,today, so let's dive straight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.04,0:00:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.67,0:00:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to start by talking
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about developing and debugging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.65,0:00:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at our typical
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.63,0:00:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,development configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.72,0:00:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got our Mac running Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.05,0:00:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and nearby we have the device
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.97,0:00:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're developing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.66,0:00:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Connecting the two we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.56,0:00:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar white cable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.83,0:00:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this configuration has
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.21,0:00:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,suited us very well for almost
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.01,0:00:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ten years now, but more and more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:00:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,developers are finding needs to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be more mobile while debugging
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.36,0:01:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with their devices, and to make
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.74,0:01:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this easier, I'm proud to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.20,0:01:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,announce that with Xcode 9 that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.74,0:01:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,white cable is no longer needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.52,0:01:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.82,0:01:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is now possible to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.37,0:01:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and debug on your device over
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.90,0:01:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wi-Fi, and we call this wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.17,0:01:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,development.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.75,0:01:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So who can take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,wireless development?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.35,0:01:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we think many developers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.51,0:01:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to love it, but here
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.69,0:01:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are some obvious examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.79,0:01:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,With the introduction of ARKit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.43,0:01:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this week, I'm sure many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are eager to sit down and build
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.32,0:01:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,an augmented reality app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.42,0:01:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,While debugging your app you're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.23,0:01:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,going to need to be moving
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.20,0:01:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,around more than you might be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,used to, holding your phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.34,0:01:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,doing this kind of thing, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.89,0:01:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,being able to get away from the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,computer to do this will make
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.44,0:01:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that much easier than it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.80,0:01:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:01:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you building
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.46,0:01:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,fitness apps, you probably know
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.41,0:02:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that the best way to test and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.16,0:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,debug your fitness app is for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the athlete to wear the device
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.68,0:02:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on them while they work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.03,0:02:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Being untethered from the Mac
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.16,0:02:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will make this much easier as
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you building apps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.96,0:02:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for accessories, I'm happy to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.28,0:02:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you that you are finally
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,able to debug your app on the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.83,0:02:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,device
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.11,0:02:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,while the accessory's plugged in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Lightning port.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.52,0:02:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.14,0:02:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We think accessory makers are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.30,0:02:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,going to love wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,development.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.23,0:02:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the rest of us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.55,0:02:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,convenience will be a big factor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.33,0:02:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in choosing when to go wireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.75,0:02:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't always remember to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.99,0:02:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,bring our cables with us or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.69,0:02:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes the Lightning port is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.78,0:02:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in use for some other purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.76,0:02:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, just having the option
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.15,0:02:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to jump on a Wi-Fi network to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,continue developing and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.40,0:02:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,debugging on our device, will be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.78,0:02:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's not only iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.98,0:02:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,developers who can enjoy this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.85,0:02:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wirelessly connected Apple TVs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.27,0:02:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are also supported.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.52,0:03:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.05,0:03:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So now Apple TV developers can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.57,0:03:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,develop and debug on their Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,TVs over Wi-Fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.46,0:03:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV developers, your living
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.26,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,room is now your development
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit back and relax on your couch
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.91,0:03:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,while you build the next great
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV game
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.02,0:03:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.16,0:03:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.31,0:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to stretch
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.49,0:03:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,cables across the room, to trip
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.25,0:03:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,over your kids or roommates or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.51,0:03:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,dogs or cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We think Apple TV developers are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.92,0:03:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,going to love wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.05,0:03:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,development, and we can't wait
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the next great Apple TV
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.49,0:03:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,game that you build while
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.31,0:03:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,relaxing in your living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.24,0:03:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you need to be able
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to take advantage of wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,development?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.16,0:03:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you just need an iPhone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad or iPod touch, running iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.71,0:03:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,11 or an Apple TV running tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.99,0:03:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.53,0:03:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the Mac you just need to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.74,0:03:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,be running macOS 10.12.4 or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.06,0:03:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What about tools support?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Xcode has extensive
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.66,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,support for wirelessly connected
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.26,0:04:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.21,0:04:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Xcode treats a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,wirelessly connected device in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the same way as a USB
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,connected device, so all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,device actions will just work,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.67,0:04:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,installing and running your app
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.04,0:04:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on the device, of course, as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,well as debugging your app, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.86,0:04:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,this includes all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.99,0:04:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced debugging features,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,such as V debugging, Memory
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Graph debugging and GP Frame
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.35,0:04:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,debugging.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Profiling in instruments works
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,great as well, and other tools
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.13,0:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that also support wirelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,connected devices, include
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.04,0:04:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Inspector, Console
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.21,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and Configurator.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For tvOS developers, Safari Web
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.05,0:04:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector supports wirelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.37,0:04:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,connected Apple TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.83,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is great news for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,TVMLKit developers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.86,0:04:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And QuickTime screen recording
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,also supports wirelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,connected Apple TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.44,0:04:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, while we're calling this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.29,0:04:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,wireless development, strictly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:04:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking, you're not limited to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,only connecting your devices
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.67,0:04:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over Wi-Fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:04:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,While Wi-Fi will be a popular
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,choice, for those of us that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.96,0:05:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,support it, Ethernet will work
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,great as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.67,0:05:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, any combination of Wi-Fi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ethernet to connect your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.06,0:05:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,device and your Mac over the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,network works great, provided
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that your Mac and your device
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,can connect to each other over
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that network.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.66,0:05:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And just to be clear, the option
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.92,0:05:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to connect your devices over USB
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.68,0:05:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,remains as it always has been.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are now all your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,options for connecting your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,devices with your development
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.27,0:05:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's just been a brief
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.16,0:05:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,introduction to wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.59,0:05:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,development.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.26,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, to give you details on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,how to pair your devices and to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.25,0:05:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about the workflow, I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.29,0:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,like to invite up Breckin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.11,0:05:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Chris.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've been working really
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,hard on wireless development for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.88,0:05:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode 9, and I can't wait to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:05:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about it with you, so let's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:05:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you set up your device
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.81,0:06:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for wireless development?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's really easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go to the Devices and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.44,0:06:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Simulators window and connect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your device to your Mac with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,your Lightning or USB cable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The device will show up, as it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.63,0:06:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,always has, but you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.39,0:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a new option.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.05,0:06:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Connect via network.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.25,0:06:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just enable this option and if
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.78,0:06:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the device and the Mac are on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the same network, after a few
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.49,0:06:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,moments you'll see a globe icon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.32,0:06:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,appear to the right of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.23,0:06:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once this globe icon appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you can unplug your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.60,0:06:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cable and continue developing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your app completely wirelessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this works identically for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.35,0:06:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone, iPad, iPod touch and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.37,0:06:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV, but for Apple TV
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.17,0:06:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So as Chris mentioned, a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:06:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,our Apple TVs, they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:06:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on our desks, they're in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,our entertainment center and,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you've got your cables
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.52,0:07:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,set up just the way you want
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.50,0:07:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,them, all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.95,0:07:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing you want to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,reach back there and unplug
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,everything and connect a USB-C
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.87,0:07:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,cable, so luckily for Apple TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We support wireless pairing in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.39,0:07:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Discovery, so to do that all you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.34,0:07:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do is go to the Remote
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.97,0:07:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,App and Devices screen on your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.15,0:07:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.01,0:07:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you go there, go back to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.87,0:07:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the Devices and Simulators
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,window in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That Apple TV will appear as a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered device automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you select that device, a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,pin code will appear on your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just put that pin code in and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.93,0:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,click Connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After you connect it will be the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.55,0:07:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,same as if you had paired with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it via USB-C cable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.81,0:07:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We think this is great for Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.28,0:07:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,TV development.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.64,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.24,0:07:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's getting paired, but I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:07:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,know some of you are wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.72,0:07:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, is it really that easy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.85,0:08:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to connect, and the answer for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.75,0:08:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,almost everyone is absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So for most home and small
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.94,0:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,business networks no
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,configuration is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make sure that your Mac and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.18,0:08:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your devices are on the same
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.19,0:08:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,network and everything just
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.23,0:08:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know some of you work on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,more complex networks, say
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.04,0:08:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,corporate, large institutional
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,networks, and if your system
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.63,0:08:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,administrator has set up certain
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,restrictions, it may be a little
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.81,0:08:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,more difficult, but not by much
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because we now support
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,connecting directly by IP
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.23,0:08:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,address to your device.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.04,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite as easy as doing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing, but all you have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.78,0:08:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is Control click on the device
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.29,0:08:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Devices and Simulators
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.35,0:08:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,window and you'll see a Connect
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.69,0:08:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,via IP address option.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.85,0:08:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just click that and then go to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.72,0:08:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your settings on your device,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.30,0:08:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,get your IP address, enter it in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:08:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.95,0:08:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So adds a little bit of a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.74,0:08:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,technical aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can ping the device from
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.85,0:09:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Mac, you're probably good to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you want any of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.84,0:09:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper details as far as ports,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe to pass to your system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,administrator, please check out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the wireless development
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.17,0:09:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,documentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got all of that detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.41,0:09:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, to reiterate, for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,almost everyone almost all of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.86,0:09:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the time you won't need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.42,0:09:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.25,0:09:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So now that we have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.61,0:09:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,connectivity and pairing out of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.72,0:09:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the way, it's time to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,work on your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.79,0:09:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So to do that, well, nothing's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,really changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just select your device in the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.83,0:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Devices list, only now, when
